---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Consulting" description="Specification engineering, context engineering, and intent engineering for teams building with AI agents.">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Everyone is talking about how to run more agents faster.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Nobody is talking about how to run them well.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p>
      AI capabilities are outpacing adoption. Most organizations can build agents
      that work — fewer can build agents that work <em>well</em>, consistently, at scale,
      under real constraints. The gap between what's possible and what's deployed is where
      the real work lives. I help close that gap.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Why Organizations Get Stuck</h2>
    <p>Four forces keep capable teams from deploying AI well.</p>

    <div class="inertia-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Regulatory</h3>
        <p>COPPA, HIPAA, GDPR. Rules written for a world before agents. Procurement cycles measured in years, not sprints.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Organizational</h3>
        <p>18 months from "this saves $10M/year" to saving it. Pilot programs, change management, internal politics.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Cultural</h3>
        <p>Most teams treat AI as a tool, not a discipline. Adoption requires muscle memory, not just better models.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Trust</h3>
        <p>Verification at scale is expensive. Moving from "I do the work" to "I verify AI work" requires guardrails and oversight infrastructure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>How We Work</h2>
    <p>Four disciplines, each building on the last.</p>

    <div class="discipline-stack">
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">1</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Prompt Craft</h3>
          <p>Clear instructions, examples, guardrails. Table stakes. Necessary, not sufficient.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">2</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Context Engineering</h3>
          <p>Curating the information environment agents operate within. System prompts, memory architecture, MCP servers, retrieval design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">3</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Intent Engineering</h3>
          <p>Encoding organizational purpose, values, and decision boundaries into agent infrastructure. Not what agents <em>can</em> do — what they <em>should</em> do.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="level-card">
        <div class="level-number">4</div>
        <div class="level-content">
          <h3>Specification Engineering</h3>
          <p>Writing documents autonomous agents can execute against over extended time horizons. The difference between a demo and a deployment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="bridge-text">
      Most organizations are strong at Level 1, aware of Level 2, and have never considered
      Levels 3 or 4. We help you build the full stack.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Digital Toolkits</h2>
    <p>Practical frameworks for teams building with AI agents. Each toolkit is a digital PDF — templates, checklists, and decision structures you can use immediately.</p>

    <div class="bundle-card">
      <div class="bundle-badge">The Complete Practice</div>
      <h3>Trust Architecture Complete</h3>
      <div class="bundle-pricing">
        <span class="bundle-price">$149</span>
        <span class="bundle-compare">$196 individually</span>
      </div>
      <p>All four trust architecture products in one package — identity, voice, governance, and restraint. Start with the Blueprint for the overview, then go deeper with each dimension.</p>
      <p class="bundle-includes">Includes: Trust Architecture Blueprint + Agent Voice Architecture Guide + Agent Governance Starter Kit + Agent Restraint Specification</p>
      <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/aFacN5aRi3n7aC809624007" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
    </div>

    <div class="toolkits-grid">
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Evaluation Design</span>
        <h3>Sovereignty Assessment Toolkit</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>47-point checklist across 7 domains, scoring rubric, and action plan template for evaluating whether technology honors human sovereignty.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/8x2cN5aRi0aV11yf4024001" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Specification Engineering</span>
        <h3>Trust Architecture Blueprint</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>Four-pillar framework for building trust into autonomous systems — identity, memory, governance, and refusal rights.</p>
        <p class="toolkit-fit">This is for you if you are building agents and have never defined who they are, what they remember, or what they can refuse.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/5kQdR91gIg9TaC84pm24002" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Intent Engineering</span>
        <h3>Agent Voice Architecture Guide</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>Voice design principles, extraction vs. sovereignty language, voice specification templates, and quality checks.</p>
        <p class="toolkit-fit">This is for you if you have never made a deliberate decision about how your agents speak — and something about their tone has been bothering you.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/bJe5kDgbC7Dn4dK7By24003" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Constraint Architecture</span>
        <h3>Agent Governance Starter Kit</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>Charter template, boundary specification, drift monitoring, four-level accountability, and authority structure.</p>
        <p class="toolkit-fit">This is for you if your agents make decisions and take actions but there is no written charter, no boundary map, and no accountability process.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/5kQ14ngbC0aVh0wf4024004" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Constraint Architecture</span>
        <h3>Agent Restraint Specification</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>Boundary audit, refusal categories, fail-mode matrix, accountability architecture, and adversarial testing.</p>
        <p class="toolkit-fit">This is for you if your agents can do more than they should — and you have been relying on good intentions instead of written boundaries.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/3cIaEX3oQcXHaC82he24005" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
      <div class="toolkit-card">
        <span class="discipline-badge">Context Engineering</span>
        <h3>Agent Memory Architecture Guide</h3>
        <p class="toolkit-price">$49</p>
        <p>Memory types, governance templates, session protocols, the canonical rule for resolving conflicts, and retention policies.</p>
        <p class="toolkit-fit">This is for you if your agents remember everything by default and you have never decided what they should forget — or who controls that decision.</p>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/14A9AT6B2bTDh0wcVS24006" class="btn btn-primary mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Now</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
      Each toolkit includes an interactive Claude Code skill. <a href="/skills">See all skills &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Services</h2>

    <div class="guarantee">
      <strong>The Guarantee:</strong> If an assessment or audit doesn't surface at least 3 actionable findings, you pay nothing.
    </div>

    <h3>Assessments & Audits</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Four-Discipline Audit <span class="discipline-badge">Full Practice</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Evaluate your team's prompt craft, context engineering, intent engineering, and specification maturity.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Context Engineering Review <span class="discipline-badge">Context Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Audit your agent memory, retrieval, system prompts, and information environment.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Privacy Architecture Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Map your data flows, consent patterns, encryption coverage, and minimization gaps. Delivered as a prioritized findings report.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Security Code Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Audit authentication, session management, encryption implementation, and rate limiting. Delivered as a fixes list ranked by severity.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">COPPA Technical Review</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Assess your age-gating, parental consent flows, data collection, and retention against current COPPA requirements. Delivered as an implementation roadmap.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Workshops</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Intent Engineering Workshop <span class="discipline-badge">Intent Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day workshop on encoding values and decision boundaries into agent systems.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Sovereignty Assessment Workshop <span class="discipline-badge">Evaluation Design</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day guided sovereignty assessment on your product with your team.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Sovereignty-Honoring Design</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day training on building products that honor user autonomy. Includes framework, exercises, and recording.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Child Safety Implementation</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Half-day training on age-gating, consent flows, and data protection for products serving children. Includes code templates and implementation guide.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$4,500</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Implementation</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Specification Engineering Sprint <span class="discipline-badge">Specification Engineering</span></div>
        <div class="service-desc">One-week sprint producing agent specifications your team can deploy against.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$5,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Child Safety Build Support</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Hands-on implementation of age gates, parental consent flows, and data protection. Built alongside your engineering team over 2-4 weeks.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$12,000</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Ethical AI Architecture</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Design and build multi-agent systems with governance, identity architecture, drift monitoring, and alignment verification.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$20,000</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="mt-lg">Retainer</h3>
    <div class="services-list">
      <div class="service-item">
        <div class="service-name">Advisory</div>
        <div class="service-desc">8 hours/month + async support.</div>
        <div class="service-price">$3,500/mo</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
      I focus on technical implementation — not legal advice. For legal interpretation
      of COPPA, GDPR, or other regulations, please consult a qualified attorney.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <h2>Let's Talk</h2>
    <p>Free 30-minute discovery call to discuss your needs.</p>
    <div class="cta-buttons mt-md">
      <a href="/fit" class="btn">Check Project Fit</a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/evoked/discovery-call" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule a Call</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Discipline badge — small pill on toolkit cards and service names */
  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  /* Inertia forces grid — reuses focus-grid pattern */
  .inertia-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .inertia-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .inertia-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Discipline stack — vertical cumulative cards */
  .discipline-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .level-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-smooth);
  }

  .level-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-accent);
  }

  .level-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .level-content h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .level-content p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .bridge-text {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Services list — card-style for mobile-friendliness */
  .services-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .service-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .service-name {
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .service-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
  }

  .service-price {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  /* Existing styles carried forward */
  .guarantee {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .guarantee strong {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .toolkits-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .toolkit-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--border-accent);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .toolkit-card:first-child {
    border-color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .toolkit-card h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .toolkit-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  .toolkit-price {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
  }

  .toolkit-fit {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .toolkit-card .btn {
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .bundle-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-warm);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    position: relative;
  }

  .bundle-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .bundle-card h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
  }

  .bundle-pricing {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .bundle-price {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
  }

  .bundle-compare {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: line-through;
  }

  .bundle-includes {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Responsive: services stack on mobile */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .service-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }

    .service-price {
      margin-left: 0;
    }

    .level-card {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .level-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
